Ah, I suppose that's what the "OCI runtime error" prefix was trying to say.

I believe their code actually answers why the error message is showing up. They assume that rootful stuff shouldn't be done if we're already in a userns, falling back to rootless-as-root I guess. And I am in fact inside a userns because Chromebook Linux beta is implemented with LXC.

```
	// euid = 0, in a userns.
	// As we are unaware of cgroups path, we can't determine whether we have the full
	// access to the cgroups path.
	// Either way, we can safely decide to use the rootless cgroups manager.
```

Ok, I'll file with upstream after more testing, and see how they feel about this. It does seem like runc already has an escape hatch of [a 'rootless' bool](https://github.com/opencontainers/runc/blob/5efdc0c5a42d7965141271448dba6af4e1429962/rootless_linux.go#L14) which I assume can't be reached through podman as is?
